org.prebake.util
Class SyncLinkedList<T extends SyncListElement<T>>

java.lang.Object
  org.prebake.util.SyncLinkedList<T>

public final class SyncLinkedList<T extends SyncListElement<T>>
extends java.lang.Object

This is a quick and dirty synchronized linked list that provides O(1) insert and remove operations, and single-direction traversal that is O(1) amortized and O(n) non-amortized worst-case where n is the number of items that have been removed since last traversal. (The amortized time assumes traversals are at least as common as removals.)

Caveats

The operations below are synchronized per list, so if elements are moved from one list to another, the mover must be synchronized externally on both lists. Best not to do that.
